Comment: Dear Patty, tonight in Canada there are:
Thousands of children living below the poverty line and going hungry;
Whole communities going without running, potable water;
Veterans struggling with seen and unseen wounds of war;
Whole families (especially in Ontario) choosing to spend their diminished paycheques on either heat, light or food.
Amid this depressing season you (and your clueless assistant) emerge as the latest in a growing list of Liberal parasites sucking the taxpayers dry.
You, ma'am, are a disgusting piece of work.
Resign.

Comment: Hi Doug... I read through your link to the Federal Government's forestry management site. Could not find anything which outlined the replacement of nutrients which are lost to shipping product away from the forest. 

As far as I could tell by reading through the first few pages, if you:
1.  printed out a plan to chop down a forest;
2.  chop down the forest;
3.  monitor it while you watch it grow back;
4.  report the results of your 'monitoring;' 
5. wait until enough of the forest to grow back that it is profitable to chop it all down again,
...then you can start all over again. Nothing about replacing the nutrients you shipped away, or how they would be replaced naturally.
